        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 27 at 11:01AM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>At 1100 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
Santa Elena, or 12 miles southeast of Agua Nueva, moving northeast at
35 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 50 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
San Isidro, San Rafael Ranch Airport, Santa Elena, and Puesta Del Sol
Airport.

This includes US Highway 281 near mile marker 728.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

Frequent cloud to ground lightning is occurring with this storm.
Lightning can strike 10 miles away from a thunderstorm. Seek a safe
shelter inside a building or vehicle.</instruction>
